    "subtype": "equipment",
    "text": "The traditional headwear for the Red Mantis assassin is the *mask of the mantis*. Most of these masks are constructed from hard leather helmets that serve to obscure the assassin's identity and give them the appearance of possessing a mantis's head. Some variants, however, consist only of the mask itself, and are meant to be worn over the face. Regardless of the shape and style, all *masks of the mantis* function the same.  \n  \n Members of the Vernai can use any mask of the mantis to enhance their frightening presence\u2014something they often do simply to reveal their standing in the society without speaking a word, as detailed fully in the entry for Vernai's Ire activation below.  \n  \n While wearing a *mask of the mantis*, you gain a +1 item bonus to Perception checks.",
    "traits": [
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 159,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "uncommon"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "f31704572455b8d77a8bd97c0045fde6",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "links": [
          {
            "alt": "Recall Knowledge",
            "aonid": 26,
            "game-obj": "Actions",
            "name": "Recall Knowledge",
            "type": "link"
          }
        ],
        "name": "Uncommon",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 11",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 11",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 11,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Something of uncommon rarity requires special training or comes from a particular culture or part of the world. Some character choices give access to uncommon options, and the GM can choose to allow access for anyone. Less is known about uncommon creatures than common creatures. They typically can't be summoned. The DC of Recall Knowledge checks related to these creature is increased by 2.",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 98,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "56b56ea5f9d865dc549f0ed7372ab504",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "links": [
          {
            "alt": "invest",
            "aonid": 2799,
            "game-obj": "Actions",
            "name": "invest",
            "type": "link"
          }
        ],
        "name": "Invested",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 218,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "GM Core pg. 219",
              "aonid": 218,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "GM Core pg. 219",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "GM Core",
            "page": 219,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "A character can invest only 10 magical items that have the invested trait. None of the magical effects of the item apply if the character hasn\u2019t invested it, nor can it be activated, though the character still gains any normal benefits from wearing the physical item (like a hat keeping rain off their head).",
        "type": "trait"
      },
      {
        "alternate_link": {
          "alternate_type": "legacy",
          "aonid": 103,
          "game-obj": "Traits",
          "type": "alternate_link"
        },
        "classes": [
          "trait"
        ],
        "edition": "remastered",
        "game-id": "15e2d048ce93e7b648064b09972535bc",
        "game-obj": "Traits",
        "name": "Magical",
        "sources": [
          {
            "errata": {
              "alt": "2.0",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "2.0",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "link": {
              "alt": "Player Core pg. 458",
              "aonid": 216,
              "game-obj": "Sources",
              "name": "Player Core pg. 458",
              "type": "link"
            },
            "name": "Player Core",
            "page": 458,
            "type": "source"
          }
        ],
        "text": "Something with the magical trait is imbued with magical energies not tied to a specific tradition of magic. Some items or effects are closely tied to a particular tradition of magic. In these cases, the item has the arcane, divine, occult, or primal trait instead of the magical trait. Any of these traits indicate that the item is magical.",
        "type": "trait"
      }
    ],
